data.meta_desc: In the 1930s and for several following decades western Pennsylvania became home to the myth of Charlie No-Face' also known as The Green Man. Accordingly to the story of Char;ie No-Face, it was said he could be found walking up and down a quiet stretch of the State Route 351 in the middle of the night. Sadly it wasn't just a myth. Charlie No- Face turned out to be a real man who was named Raymond Robinson. When he was 9 years old Raymond was injured by an electrical line and lost his eyes nose and right arm. To avoid scaring people he would go out at night for long walks. He was said to be a friendly and well-liked man. Memes.
